{
  "name": "Innocuous Aspect",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Genjutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You create an area of false visions that encompasses all willing creature in a 20-foot radius centered on you, of your choice. You do not need to spend chakra to maintain concentration on this jutsu. You and each affected creature takes on the appearance of a harmless creature or object of your choice. Each image is identical and only appearance is affected. Sound, movement or physical inspection can reveal that this is a genjutsu. A creature that uses its action to study the image visually can determine that it is an illusion with a successful wisdom (Illusions) check vs your Genjutsu save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, that creature sees through the image.</p>",
